[] a owl:Axiom ;
    ns3:evidence <http://model.geneontology.org/5745387b00001750/586fc17a00001344> ;
    dc:contributor "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196"^^xsd:string ;
    dc:date "2017-03-06"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:comment "PMID:9003776: (ES): Fragments of LAG-1 and intracellular GLP-1 clearly interact in yeast two-hybrid experiments (Table II)."^^xsd:string,
        "PMID:9003776: (ES): With S-Tag-GLP-1 (ANK), retention of LAG-1 (199-673) was poor (Figure 6, lane 2), but with S-Tag-GLP-1 (RAM/ANK) retention of the LAG-1 (199-673) was efficient (Figure 6, lane 3)."^^xsd:string ;
    owl:annotatedProperty ns1:RO_0002233 ;
    owl:annotatedSource <http://model.geneontology.org/5745387b00001750/586fc17a00001179> ;
    owl:annotatedTarget <http://model.geneontology.org/5745387b00001750/586fc17a00001181> .

[] a owl:Axiom ;
    ns3:evidence <http://model.geneontology.org/5745387b00001750/586fc17a00001469>,
        <http://model.geneontology.org/5745387b00001750/586fc17a00001470>,
        <http://model.geneontology.org/5745387b00001750/586fc17a00001471> ;
    dc:contributor "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196"^^xsd:string ;
    dc:date "2017-03-13"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:comment "PMID:10830967 (ES): The sterility of lag-3(RNAi) adults resulted from a failure of germline proliferation (Fig. 3d,e), a phenotype typical of glp-1 null mutants; the protruding vulva (Fig. 3f) was similar to that of lin-12 loss-of-function mutants."^^xsd:string,
        "PMID:1769331 (ES): For weak lag-1 and lag-2 mutants, adults were often found in which the germ line had failed to proliferate.  In these animals, there was no mitotic germ line; instead germ cells that would normally be in mitosis entered meiosis and differentiated into sperm (Fig. 5)."^^xsd:string,
        "PMID:3677168 (ES): The glp-1 mutations each affect proliferation of the germ line in essentially the same way:  germ cells that would normally continue to divide mitotically instead enter meiosis and differentiate into gametes (Table 1; Figure 2)."^^xsd:string ;
    owl:annotatedProperty ns1:RO_0002213 ;
    owl:annotatedSource <http://model.geneontology.org/5745387b00001750/586fc17a00000995> ;
    owl:annotatedTarget <http://model.geneontology.org/5745387b00001750/5745387b00001754> .

